 valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Resist gear - Why have it and What to get?</span><hr size=1> As a melee, if you aren't a &quot;main tank&quot; against the dragon, forget AC and HP and go for resists. Most times, if you know what you are doing, you'll only get hit two or three times by Vox or Naggy, and AC won't help much in that. It's the AOE's that you have to worry about. They usually melee for around 225, but others will get aggro before you die, if you turn off auto attack the minute it turns its attentions on you. However, the AOE's can do up to 1200 or so hit points if not resisted; the higher your resists, the less damage you'll take. <br>
<br>
On my first raid (yes, the old one is reminiscing now), I was only level 39 (I was leading it, so couldn't not go for level). I was feared almost constantly, even with higher than a 70 magic resist. The next dragon raid I was 40, and just the difference in one level meant my time being feared was cut in half. The more levels I got, the easier it was to resist the fear, especially if I kept my magic resist up. By the time I was 49, I'd have fights in which I was feared for less than 1 second only once during the battle. <br>
<br>
Resists are everything if you aren't the main tank. <p>Haemish MacLennan<br>
Founder<Br>
